Description:
    Upgrades an existing Angarium installation to the current schema.

    New applications use `angarium:install`. Applications that installed an
    earlier version run this to pick up any migrations they are missing.
    Copying is idempotent: a migration that already exists in the target app
    (db/migrate or db/NAME_migrate) is skipped, not duplicated. Legacy
    installs that copied migrations with Rails' native migration copy (files
    named `<ts>_name.angarium.rb`) are also recognized and skipped.

    Multi-database aware: with --database (or config.database recorded in
    config/initializers/angarium.rb by a previous install), missing
    migrations are copied into db/NAME_migrate instead of db/migrate.

Example:
    bin/rails g angarium:upgrade
    bin/rails db:migrate
